<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Thursday on the New York Stock Exchange, American Stock 
Exchange and Nasdaq Stock Market. 

</P>
<P>
 *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Toro Co. rose 1 3/8 to 34 3/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Toro, a maker of lawnmowers and other yard equipment, said it  
expects second-quarter and full-year earnings to beat analysts' 
estimates, due to cost-cutting and an effort to improve profit 
margins. 

</P>
<P>
 *Silverleaf Resorts fell 5/8 to 6 7/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The resort operator said it expects earnings in the second and  
third quarter to miss analysts' expectations by 6 to 8 cents per 
share. The company cited higher sales and marketing expenses. 

</P>
<P>
 *Delco Remy rose 1 to 10 5/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The company earned 32 cents per share in its most recent  
quarter, beating analysts' expectations by a penny. Delco Remy 
makes electrical and power-train components for automobiles. 

</P>
<P>
 *ContiFinancial Corp. rose 1 1/4 to 8 9/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Residential Funding Corp., a finance unit of General Motors,  
wants to acquire ContiFinancial, a loan originator. ContiFinancial 
has signed an ``indication of interest'' letter, which amounts to a 
tentative agreement. 

</P>
<P>
 *AMEX    	

</P>
<P>
 *Devon Energy Corp. rose 2 1/4 to 33 3/4  
</P>
<P>
 *PennzEnergy Co. fell 1/8 to 14 1/2 on the NYSE 
</P>
<P>
	Devon plans to acquire PennzEnergy, the former exploration and  
production business of Pennzoil Co., for $675 million. 

</P>
<P>
 *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Healtheon rose 20 3/8 to 100 3/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Healtheon will merge with WebMD Inc. in an estimated $5.7  
billion stock swap, creating an Internet company offering health 
care services and information for consumers, doctors, insurers and 
drug makers. 

</P>
<P>
 *Adam Software Inc. rose 3 to 26 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	Adam.com, another online provider of health information, secured  
an alliance with Cox Interactive Media. Adam.com will provide 
localized editorial content for Cox's network of sites on the World 
Wide Web. 

</P>
<P>
 *Etec Systems Inc. fell 5 5/8 to 30 3/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The chip-equipment maker reported a loss of 29 cents per share  
in its most recent quarter, compared to a profit of 47 cents in the 
same period last year. Etec said its existing orders don't indicate 
an immediate recovery. 

</P>
<P>
 *EToys, priced at 20, rose to 76 9/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The online toy retailer raised $166 million in a  
much-anticipated initial public offering. EToys had raised both the 
size and the price range of its offering on Wednesday, citing heavy 
demand. 


</P>
