Staff on Oct. 1, 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	A 6-foot-5-inch North Carolina native, Shelton is a decorated  
Vietnam combat veteran and former commander of the U.S. Special 
Operations Command, which oversees the Army's Green Berets, the 
Navy's Seals and other elite outfits. 
</P>
<P>
	As head of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, Shelton has a leading  
voice in the U.S. role in NATO's air war against Yugoslavia, 
although he has no direct command of troops. He and the rest of the 
Joint Chiefs met in the Pentagon on Thursday with Gen. Wesley 
Clark, the top NATO commander and architect of the air campaign. 
</P>
<P>
	Shelton, in a statement issued at the Pentagon, said: ``It has  
been a particular privilege to represent our nation's soldiers, 
sailors, airmen and Marines during a period of great international 
uncertainty and an unprecedented pace of military operations.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
