<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-20 20:11:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ventura Hits 2 Slams in Doubleheader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Robin Ventura became the first major leaguer to  
hit grand slams in both games of a doubleheader, doing it for the 
New York Mets on Thursday night against the Milwaukee Brewers. 
</P>
<P>
	Ventura hit his first slam against Jim Abbott in the first  
inning of the opener. He hit a 3-2 pitch high down the right-field 
line, just over the outstretched glove of Jeromy Burnitz, in an 
11-10 win. 
</P>
<P>
	Ventura came up with the bases loaded in the fourth inning of  
the nightcap. He again worked the count full before hitting another 
high fly down the right-field line off Horacio Estrada that Burnitz 
couldn't jump for. 
</P>
<P>
	The two slams gave Ventura a total of 12 in his career, one  
behind Harold Baines for the active lead. Mark McGwire and Ken 
Griffey Jr. also have 12. 
</P>
<P>
	Ventura also became the first player ever to twice hit two slams  
in a day. He had two slams in a game for the Chicago White Sox at 
Texas on Sept. 4, 1995. 
</P>
<P>
	This is the third time this season a player has hit two slams in  
one day. Ventura joined St. Louis' Fernando Tatis, who did it in 
one inning against Los Angeles on April 23, and Boston's Nomar 
Garciaparra, who did it May 10 against Seattle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
