<HEADLINE> London Shares Close Higher / British Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Share prices rose on the London Stock Exchange on  
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Financial Times Stock Exchange 100-share index closed up  
101.50 points, or 1.6 percent, at 6,368.20. 
</P>
<P>
	Provisional market volume was 943 million shares compared with 1  
billion shares on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Heavily weighted companies in the telecommunications and  
financial sectors pushed the index to session highs late in the 
day. Hopes for further interest rate cuts helped lift the financial 
sector. 
</P>
