<HEADLINE> Sitcom Actor Dick Charged in Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- ``NewsRadio'' actor Andy Dick was charged  
with driving into a utility pole while under the influence of 
alcohol and drugs, then trying to run away. 
</P>
<P>
	Dick, 33, who plays a neurotic, whiny reporter on the NBC  
sitcom, was freed on $10,000 bail after his arrest Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	The actor tried to run away but was chased by a witness who held  
him until officers came to arrest him. 
</P>
<P>
	Dick was charged with cocaine and marijuana possession, driving  
under the influence and hit-and-run driving. 
