<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Milne Signs Extension With Bengals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- Fullback Brian Milne signed a one-year  
contract extension Thursday with the Cincinnati Bengals. 
</P>
<P>
	The Bengals also waived receiver Jason Shelley, a first-year  
free agent from Central State, Ohio. Shelley was in the Dallas 
Cowboys' training camp in 1996-97 and signed with the Bengals April 
22. 
</P>
<P>
	Milne, a restricted free agent, started 14 games last season  
after being slowed by a bad back. He carried 10 times for 41 yards 
and had 26 catches for 124 yards. 
</P>
