<HEADLINE> Olivetti Nears Telecom Takeover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Olivetti appeared poised to meet its goal for  
acquiring a controlling stake in Telecom Italia as its $65 billion 
offer to acquire its larger rival was set to expire today. 
</P>
<P>
	Analysts said most shareholders would wait until the last minute  
to decide whether to accept the hostile offer. 
</P>
<P>
	Olivetti, with interests in cellular phones, office equipment  
and communications technology, has said it needs at least 35 
percent of Telecom's ordinary shares to proceed with the takeover. 
