<HEADLINE> Giants Sign Wide Receiver Fred Brock </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- The New York Giants signed free  
agent wide receiver Fred Brock on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Brock began his pro career with the Arizona Cardinals in 1996,  
spending his first season on the practice squad and appearing in 
two games in 1997, catching one pass for 29 yards. 
</P>
<P>
	Brock played in 12 games last season, finishing with two catches  
for 12 yards. He was left unprotected by the Cardinals in the 
expansion draft and selected by the Cleveland Browns, but was 
released May 4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
