<HEADLINE> Portland, Utah Set Scoring Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- The Portland Trail Blazers and Utah Jazz  
combined for just 25 points in the first quarter of their 
second-round playoff game Thursday night, breaking the NBA 
postseason record of 26 set by Detroit and Boston in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
	Portland, shooting 5-of-22 from the field, led Utah 14-11 at the  
end of the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	Utah was 4-of-17 from the field and made seven turnovers, three  
by Howard Eisley. 
</P>
<P>
	Portland set an NBA record Monday night in Game 1 for fewest  
points in any quarter when they managed just five in the fourth 
quarter of their 93-83 Game 1 loss to the Jazz. 
</P>
