<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ronaldo To Be Asked About Doctors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BRASILIA, Brazil (AP) -- Brazilian soccer star Ronaldo will be  
summoned as a witness in a investigation into why doctors then with 
Brazil's national team allowed him to play in the World Cup final 
after suffering a convulsion. 
</P>
<P>
	``Ronaldo's testimony is of fundamental importance,'' Mauro  
Brandao, president of Rio de Janeiro's Regional Medical Council, 
which is conducting the inquiry, told the Correio Braziliense 
newspaper. ``He will be summoned when he comes to Brazil to play 
for the national team.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Ronaldo, who now plays for Internazionale of Milan, will be on  
the Brazilian team for two exhibition matches against the 
Netherlands on June 5 and 8. 
</P>
<P>
	Ronaldo was hospitalized shortly before the July 12 World Cup  
final against France, and was scratched from the lineup -- then 
inexplicably put back in, apparently with the approval of the 
team's doctors. 
</P>
<P>
	He played poorly and Brazil lost 3-0. Later, Ronaldo said he had  
gone into convulsions at the hotel. 
</P>
<P>
	The medical council is trying to determine why doctors Lidio  
Toledo and Joaquim da Matta allowed the star striker to play. 
</P>
<P>
	Former coach Jorge Zagallo, team coordinator Zico, Toledo and  
Matta have already been questioned by the council. Details of their 
testimony have not been revealed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
