<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Vainsteins Wins Tour of Italy Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FOGGIA, Italy (AP) -- Romans Vainsteins of Latvia won the sixth  
and longest stage of the Tour of Italy on Thursday by edging 
Italians Fabrizio Guidi and Gabriele Missaglia with a late burst of 
speed. 
</P>
<P>
	Frenchman Laurent Jalabert finished in the main group and held  
to the overall lead for a second day. 
</P>
<P>
	Jalabert was seven seconds ahead of Italian Danilo Di Luca with  
16 stages left. Davide Rebellin was third, 14 seconds behind 
Jalabert. 
</P>
<P>
	Vainsteins completed the 159 miles from Lauria in 5 hours, 55  
minutes, 43 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
	Two leading contenders for overall title, defending champion  
Marco Pantani and 1997 winner Ivan Gotti, finished the day's race 
in the main group. 
</P>
<P>
	Pantani was fifth in the standings and Gotti seventh. Both  
trailed Jalabert by 16 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
	Vainsteins was in 38th place, 1:54 off the pace.  
</P>
</TEXT>
