<HEADLINE> Senate Roll Call on Gun Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	The 73-25 roll call by which the Senate voted to approve the  
juvenile justice bill, which includes numerous gun control 
provisions. On this vote, a ``yes'' vote was a vote to pass the 
bill and a ``no'' vote was a vote to kill it. 
</P>
<P>
	Voting ``yes'' were 42 Democrats and 31 Republicans.  
</P>
<P>
	Voting ``no'' were 2 Democrats and 23 Republicans.  

</P>
