<HEADLINE> Mellencamp Helps Fund-Raiser </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BILLINGS, Mont. (AP) -- On his way out of town after a concert,  
John Mellencamp made a donation to a fund-raiser for a school music 
program. 
</P>
<P>
	For weeks, parents and students at Bench Elementary have been  
putting together items for a silent auction. 
</P>
<P>
	On Monday, just hours before Mellencamp was to perform in  
Billings, Missy Jones and her daughter, Karli, dashed off a letter 
to Mellencamp, telling him about the fund-raiser. They managed to 
get the letter to one of Mellencamp's guitar players following 
warm-ups at MetraPark Arena. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones got a call Tuesday.  
</P>
<P>
	``He said, `This is John. ... John Mellencamp,''' Jones said.  
``At that point I turned into a 16-year-old saying, `Oh, my God! 
Oh, my God!''' 
</P>
<P>
	Mellencamp said he was on his way out of Billings and would  
leave an autographed copy of his new CD at the front desk of the 
Billings Sheraton for the school's benefit. 
</P>
<P>
	The CD will be the featured attraction at Friday's auction.  
</P>
</TEXT>
