<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Royals Coach Undergoes Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Kansas City Royals bullpen coach Tom  
Burgmeier will be sidelined much of the season because of injuries 
sustained in a car-bicycle accident. 
</P>
<P>
	Burgmeier, 55, was hurt while riding his bicycle to Kauffman  
Stadium on Wednesday. He underwent surgery Thursday after 
sustaining several fractures in the left knee area and two 
fractures of the right wrist. 
</P>
<P>
	Royals trainer Nick Swartz said Burgmeier's leg will be  
immobilized about two months. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's going to need extensive therapy after that to get his  
range of motion back,'' Swartz said. 
</P>
<P>
	Burgmeier's rehabilitation of the knee will be hampered by the  
wrist injury, which will make it difficult to use crutches. 
</P>
<P>
	A car turned in front of Burgmeier, the Royals said, causing him  
and the bike to become airborne over the automobile. 
</P>
</TEXT>
