<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Man Gets Life for Torture Slaying </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- A man was convicted of murder and sentenced to  
life in prison in the slaying of a retarded 59-year-old who 
prosecutors say was tortured and beaten to death in a plot to 
collect on his life insurance. 
</P>
<P>
	Terence Singleton, 28, was the fourth of six people to be tried  
in the slaying of Louis ``Buddy'' Musso, whose body was found in a 
ditch Aug. 26. Singleton was found guilty Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Three other people have been convicted on murder charges. Two  
more, including the alleged ringleader, are awaiting trial. 
</P>
<P>
	Musso died after weeks of beatings at the apartment of one of  
the defendants. He was forced to kneel naked on a mat during the 
last days of his life. Between beatings, he was denied food, bathed 
in cleaning fluids and scrubbed with a wire brush. 
</P>
<P>
	A $50,000 life insurance policy had been taken out on Musso,  
with a provision that more would be paid if he died as the result 
of violent crime. 
</P>
</TEXT>
