<HEADLINE> MTI Gets SonicNet From TCI Music </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- In the latest move to build up its presence in  
cyberspace, MTV Networks is acquiring several music Web sites from 
TCI Music, the online entertainment company controlled by cable 
magnate John Malone. 
</P>
<P>
	As part of the deal announced today, MTV will get SonicNet, a  
leading music news and information site on the Internet, along with 
several other associated sites including Addicted to Noise and 
Streamland. The sites are mainly aimed atcollege-aged listeners. 
</P>
<P>
	In return, TCI Music will get a 10 percent stake in MTV's online  
music subsidiary, which is expected to go public within the next 12 
months. TCI Music is also handing over The Box, a pay-per-view 
cable channel for music videos. 
</P>
<P>
	For MTV, the deal helps expand the footprint of its online music  
unit, which already include the Web sites for MTV and its sister 
network VH1. The subsidiary, which was formed earlier this year, is 
also developing several other online music projects. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is first and foremost an online play for us to bolster  
our position as a music player on the Internet,'' MTV chairman Tom 
Freston said in an interview. 
</P>
<P>
	The acquisition of SonicNet was the second transaction for MTV's  
fledgling online unit following its February purchase, for an 
undisclosed amount, of online broadcaster Imagine Radio, which will 
allow MTV to offer some 100 channels of Internet radio. 
</P>
<P>
	TCI Music is positioning itself as an Internet entertainment  
company with its digital music cable channel DMX and other Internet 
properties transferred from its parent company, Malone's Liberty 
Media Group, which has stakes in some 100 cable channels. In order 
to reflect its broadening beyond music and into video 
entertainment, TCI Music is renaming itself Liberty Digital. 
</P>
<P>
	MTV is owned by Viacom Inc., a media conglomerate that also owns  
the Paramount movie studio, the consumer publishing operations of 
Simon &AMP; Schuster, ``Melrose Place'' producer Spelling Entertainment 
and half of the UPN network. 
</P>
<P>
	AT&AMP;T Corp. gained ownership of Liberty Media Group as part of  
its purchase of Malone's leading cable TV company TCI. But Liberty 
continues to operate independently with its own tracking stock and 
Malone as its chairman. 

</P>
</TEXT>
