<HEADLINE> Coolio Pleas Innocent to Gun Charge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORRANCE, Calif. (AP) -- Grammy Award-winning rapper Coolio has  
pleaded innocent to charges he carried a concealed handgun in his 
car. 
</P>
<P>
	Coolio, whose real name is Artis Leon Ivey Jr., entered the plea  
Wednesday before Superior Court Judge Andrew Kauffman, who set a 
July 7 pretrial hearing. 
</P>
<P>
	The rapper pleaded innocent in February, changed to no contest  
in March, then withdrew that plea in April. No explanations were 
given. 
</P>
<P>
	Coolio was at the wheel of his Humvee in suburban Lawndale last  
September when a sheriff's deputy stopped him for allegedly driving 
on the wrong side of a street. 
</P>
<P>
	The rapper told the deputy he had a gun in a door pouch,  
prosecutors said, and the deputy seized a 9 mm semiautomatic 
pistol. 
</P>
<P>
	Coolio has a 1994 conviction for carrying a concealed firearm in  
a vehicle. The rapper won a Grammy for best rap solo in 1996 for 
``Gangsta's Paradise.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
