<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 3 in Early Trading / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened narrowly higher. The  
Dow Jones industrial average is up three points in today's early 
going. Advancers on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 3-2 lead 
over decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up eight points and the S&AMP;P 500  
Index is up one point. 
</P>
<P>
	Market watchers see a narrowly positive bias in early trading  
today. 
</P>
<P>
	Wall Street has been watching the bond market for guidance  
lately and today, bond prices are flat to slightly higher. 
</P>
<P>
	Today's trade deficit came in higher than expected, with the  
trade gap growing to $19.7 billion in March. 
</P>
<P>
	That news barely nudged the bond market.  
</P>
