<HEADLINE> Elton Brand Signs With David Falk </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Duke star Elton Brand has signed with David  
Falk, adding another big name to the agent's clientele. 
</P>
<P>
	Brand, who helped lead the Blue Devils to a 37-2 record and a  
trip to the national title game last season, left school as a 
sophomore and is certain to be one of the top picks in the NBA 
draft on June 30. 
</P>
<P>
	Falk also signed Obinna Ekezie, a 6-10 senior center from  
Maryland, the agent's office said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Brand, the consensus national college player of the year,  
averaged 17.8 points and 9.8 rebounds last season. 
</P>
<P>
	He's the first star player in this year's draft to sign with  
Falk, who also represents Michael Jordan, Patrick Ewing, Alonzo 
Mourning and other NBA stars. 
</P>
