<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Man Suffocates in Corn Bin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MECHANICSBURG, Ohio (AP) -- A farmer trying to empty a corn bin  
fell into the grain pile today and suffocated. 
</P>
<P>
	Arthur R. Bullard, 69, apparently slipped as he tried to free a  
clump of grain clogging the bin at his farm, about 30 miles west of 
Columbus. It took firefighters nearly three hours to reach Bullard. 
</P>
<P>
	Bullard, who was unloading the corn to sell, apparently went  
inside the bin at the top to check why the grain had stopped 
flowing. He had attached a rope to the bin to hang onto but 
apparently didn't tie it to himself. 
</P>
<P>
	The bin held between 10,000 and 15,000 bushels of grain.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
